MASTER DNS SERVER – BIND9
Configuramos BIND9 como servidor DNS autoritativo creando una zona directa y otra inversa para el dominio marisma.intranet.

CREACIÓN DE ZONAS
Editamos el fichero de zonas locales.
sudo nano /etc/bind/named.conf.local

Definimos la zona directa y la inversa (red 10.3.0.0/24).
    zone "marisma.intranet" {
        type master;
        file "/etc/bind/db.marisma.intranet";
    };

    zone "0.3.10.in-addr.arpa" {
        type master;
        file "/etc/bind/db.10.3.0";
    };

ZONA DIRECTA
    sudo nano /etc/bind/db.marisma.intranet
    
    $TTL 86400
    @   IN SOA ns1.marisma.intranet. admin.marisma.intranet. (
            2025010101 3600 1800 604800 86400 )
        IN NS ns1.marisma.intranet.

    ns1           IN A 10.3.0.1
    ftp1          IN A 10.3.0.2
    mail1         IN A 10.3.0.3
    mail2         IN A 10.3.0.4
    www           IN A 10.3.0.5
    departamentos IN A 10.3.0.6

    @ IN MX 10 mail1.marisma.intranet.
    @ IN MX 20 mail2.marisma.intranet.

ZONA INVERSA
    sudo nano /etc/bind/db.10.3.0

    $TTL 86400
    @   IN SOA ns1.marisma.intranet. admin.marisma.intranet. (
            2025010101 3600 1800 604800 86400 )
        IN NS ns1.marisma.intranet.

    1 IN PTR ns1.marisma.intranet.
    2 IN PTR ftp1.marisma.intranet.
    3 IN PTR mail1.marisma.intranet.
    4 IN PTR mail2.marisma.intranet.
    5 IN PTR www.marisma.intranet.
    6 IN PTR departamentos.marisma.intranet.

COMPROBACIÓN Y ARRANQUE

    sudo named-checkconf
    sudo named-checkzone marisma.intranet /etc/bind/db.marisma.intranet
    sudo named-checkzone 0.3.10.in-addr.arpa /etc/bind/db.10.3.0
    sudo systemctl restart bind9

CONFIGURACIÓN DEL CLIENTE

    sudo nano /etc/resolv.conf
    nameserver 10.3.0.1

COMPROBACIONES DNS

    nslookup -type=SOA marisma.intranet
    nslookup -type=NS marisma.intranet
    nslookup -type=MX marisma.intranet
    nslookup www.marisma.intranet
    nslookup departamentos.marisma.intranet
    nslookup 10.3.0.5
    nslookup 10.3.0.6
